r>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hatchlings</span><hr size=1> Does this sound like a good place to bring some friends and cast Jyll's a few times? <p>Darkpakt Grimsoul/45 necromancer
Doktari Hospitali/45 cleric
Ozon Fizbane/53 wizard
Ezeron Hyabusa/36 warrior

Tribunal server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 12:38:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hatchlings</span><hr size=1> The thing with the hatchlings is that if no one has been killing them, they are everywhere.. high level people running to the grey trip over the traps and just ignore them, so you'll find spots along the path to the grey that have 20-30 of the things just sitting there waiting to be slaughtered (grab some clarity and go to town). when you can find a patch of them, in 52 I can do 7-8 of them in a single bar of mana, which translates to around half a blue in 52 (little more if you have AA at 100%) which I calculate to be about the same as quadding spirocs in TD (which give you about 1/3 of a blue in 52, but only take about half a bar of mana to nuke down). Clarity makes all the differance here.. since its basically just stand up, nuke nuke nuke, sit down, if you can get clarity hatchlings can be fast xp. without clarity, go quad. personally, I just gate to the nexus and buy a hit then gate back. can almost always find a chanter in the nexus.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the real problem as I see it is finding enough of the little buggers. sure, when you first show up in the zone their easy to find, but after you clear 100 of the little guys, they get scarce. and forget running around trying to trip the traps, they only reload every half hour or so and there's only a 1 in 4 chance or so of them actually producting hatchlings. My advice? Come here if everything else is camped, clear all the hatchlings, then go somewhere else and come back another day.<br>
<br>
Still, its a nice quiet zone to spend time in. just watch out for the stone grabbers, those guys are nasty.<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 52 channeler, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 6:29:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hatchlings nerfed</span><hr size=1> Well they nerfed the trap spawn rate and the number of hatchlings that hatch from each nest with the latest patch.  5-7 used to hatch from each nest, now 2-3 hatch.  The traps only reset every 40 minutes instead of every 20 minutes.  I hate stealth nerfs like this.  Verant pisses me off sometimes.  At least announce the nerfs. <p>Kekenewah Silverbear <BR>
Level 53 High Elf Wizard (04/01/02)<BR>
Drinal server <BR>
Order of the Silver Circle guild</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/02 8:38:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hatchlings</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I thought it seemed like the traps were spawning fewer and farther between. Still, the shiknar don't despawn, so if no one has killed them for a few days, they are everywhere.... lvl 60s running to the grey spawn them all the time and don't stick around to kill them, so you can get these great big piles of them stacking up.<br>
<br>
Still, I'm not too sad about this nerf. Quadding stone grabbers is much more fun!<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 52 channeler, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/02 5:16:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hatchlings</span><hr size=1> Some druids and rangers have taken up residence in mons letalis on my server lately so the few hatchlings that do spawn are instakilled by the trackers.  Could you give me some tips on quading the stonegrabbers, they are mean and only one pounding on me often stuns me and kills me I don't know how i could survive rounding up 4 of them.  How about quading the mature rockhoppers? <p>Kekenewah Silverbear <BR>
Level 53 High Elf Wizard (04/01/02)<BR>
Drinal server <BR>
Order of the Silver Circle guild</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/02 8:28:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=421.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> stonegrabbers.</span><hr size=1> I've only done this a few times so its not like I have it down to a science yet, but it is a fun diversion and darn good xp. first off, you need sow. you *might* be able to do it with jboots/runspeed 3, but it would be iffy, stonegrabbers are fast. Also, while they find *you* all the time when you don't want them to, they can be a pain to actually find when you wat to quad them, so be perpared to cover some territory.<br>
<br>
First thing you'll want to do is head to NE corner of the zone. there's an empty spot here that is nice and wide and makes a good spot to quad them, I've quadded other places but this seems the safest. There's a trap on the east entrance to this area, so run over it a couple times and make sure its tripped, that way you dont' get a spire spirit or hatchlings join in your quad. <br>
<br>
Next head the the NW corner, find a stone grabber, tag him with you T staff and start running. Now this is the fun part.. if you let them get too far behind you you can lose agro or have them pop on top of you which can be deadly, so try to keep them not too far behind you. run around generally toward the NE corner picking up stonegrabbers as you go. it helps to double back a few times as you move toward the NE corner to get them rounded up, but BECAREFUL, they have a big range and hit sooooo hard. I made the mistake once of getting too close once while trying to round them up and in one round got beat down to 1 bubble of health. keep manaskin up, it can save you, but if you get stuned you're pretty much toast. not alot of room for error here. <br>
<br>
Anyway, once you've got 4 and they're all rounded up, its just a normal quad, snare and nuke. They still move pretty quick snared, so you'll always want to cast from max range and the Z-axis casting bug can screw you in this zone, so try to stay level with them, but they really dont have *that* many hps, so once they are snared you've got them no problem. they don't resist PoF much at all.<br>
<br>
As far as the rockhoppers go, I haven't tried quadding them yet. it seems like the mature one would be easy to quad, the trick would be to find four of them without picking up any stone grabbers. personally I think its actually going to be easier to quad stonegrabbers, just 'cause they spawn fast and are everywhere, and you have to deal with them if you'e going to hunt anything else in the zone.<br>
<br>
Its dangerous but fun, and if you get a &quot;fist of rock&quot; drop (rare from stonegrabbers) you can make a monk *VERY* happy.<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 52 channeler, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19>Soloing</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  